{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783000295,"nonce":"uykN3nNOSB4niGIOe9+rlDI5H6M=","kind":"spec","title":"Fine-grained update — search/replace blocks (design spec)"},{"type":9,"timestamp":1783000295,"nonce":"4gkqmqMRpCatdLMfkc0a4MubJCY=","label":"area:design"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1783000295,"nonce":"12nDSEM3V0OUvpIBrlv1JxnbCnU=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"create"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1783004079,"nonce":"oQjlspZGowh5+7WFV+/4JMKu7Kw=","body":"# Fine-grained update — search/replace blocks (MCP-only)\n\nQ8 decision (2026-07-02, delegated to the LLM): **search/replace blocks**.\nREVISED 2026-07-02 (Trevor): **MCP-only** — the CLI `update --patch` flag and\nthe textual `\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c SEARCH` format are REMOVED. A human doing this by hand\ndumps → `kref edit` → saves; the fine-grained path exists for agents, and\nagents reach it through `kref_patch` with structured JSON blocks. This also\ndeleted the only parser: internal/textpatch is now just the engine\n(strings.Count uniqueness gate + strings.Replace, ~55 lines).\n\n## Shipped surface\n\n- MCP: `kref_patch { id, blocks: [{search, replace}, ...] }`.\n- Semantics: exact (byte-wise) matching; each block's `search` must occur\n  **exactly once** in the current body; blocks apply in order, each against\n  the previous result; **all-or-nothing** — any failing block aborts with an\n  error naming the block and nothing is written; empty `replace` deletes;\n  empty `search` and search==replace are rejected; a patch may not leave the\n  body empty. One successful patch = one SetBody op = one new body version\n  (reported back as `version N`).\n- Rationale for content-addressed matching: a patch written against a stale\n  body fails loudly (search no longer matches) instead of clobbering a\n  concurrent edit. Uniqueness doubles as the concurrency guard.\n\n## Open question (Trevor pushback, 2026-07-02)\n\nFormat under review: Trevor worries the block format is bespoke vs. \"regular\npatches\" (unified diffs) that LLMs emit constantly, especially for docs with\nmany similar sections being bulk-replaced. Analysis + options presented in\nsession; candidate mitigation is a per-block `replace_all` (bulk-replace every\noccurrence, no uniqueness rule — mirrors Claude Code's own Edit tool) plus\nmulti-match errors that return each match's surrounding context. Alternative\nis a unified-diff tool (note: production LLM-diff appliers all discard hunk\nline numbers and locate by context — content matching in a diff costume).\nAwaiting Trevor's call; this spec updates when decided.\n"},{"type":4,"timestamp":1783004079,"nonce":"nhgApjjXuAoc9FgIAtY4epIslWM=","title":"Fine-grained update — search/replace blocks (MCP-only; format under review)"},{"type":2,"timestamp":1783004079,"nonce":"5NEWHjC41oeFDJqXKcTXS93NaUs=","status":"active"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1783005053,"nonce":"ASfqAb3lYHNfMkMIG5W/aaWV7Zk=","body":"# Fine-grained update — kref_patch: lenient unified diff (MCP-only)\n\nDecision trail, all 2026-07-02:\n1. Q8 delegated the format to the LLM → built as search/replace blocks\n   (CLI `update --patch` + `kref_patch`).\n2. Trevor: drop the CLI, MCP-only — a human dumps → `kref edit` → saves; the\n   fine-grained path exists for agents.\n3. Trevor pushback on the block format (\"LLMs sling regular patches all the\n   time\"; bulk edits in docs with many similar sections) → options presented →\n   **decision: unified diffs with a lenient applier** (aider/Codex style).\n   Shipped same day; the block format is gone.\n\n## Shipped surface\n\n`kref_patch { id, diff }` — `diff` is standard unified-diff text.\n\nLenient where LLMs are sloppy:\n- Hunk line numbers (`@@ -l,c +l,c @@`) are HINTS only, never trusted — models\n  famously get them wrong. Each hunk is located by its context/removal lines.\n- Git preamble (`diff --git`, `index`, `---`/`+++` headers), the\n  `\\ No newline at end of file` marker, and prose before the first `@@` are\n  tolerated/ignored. A bare blank line inside a hunk = blank context (mailers\n  and models strip the leading space). A junk line with no prefix is kept as\n  context — worst case it turns into a loud context-not-found error, never a\n  silent misread.\n- Context matching: exact first, then trailing-whitespace-insensitive\n  (leading whitespace stays significant — indentation is content).\n\nStrict where safety demands it:\n- Hunks apply in document order; each search starts just after the previous\n  application — this naturally walks repeated similar sections (the bulk-edit\n  case Trevor raised).\n- Ambiguity policy: several exact candidates ahead of the cursor → the line\n  hint breaks the tie (nearest wins); no usable hint → LOUD error (\"matches N\n  locations\"). Missing context (stale diff) → loud error. Never guess between\n  identical sections.\n- All-or-nothing: any failing hunk aborts the whole patch; a patch may not\n  leave the body empty. One successful patch = one SetBody = one new version.\n\n## Implementation\n\ninternal/textpatch (dep-free, ~200 lines): lenient line parser + context\nlocator + splice. We own the fuzzy locator deliberately — strict appliers\n(git apply, bluekeyes/go-gitdiff) validate the very line numbers LLMs get\nwrong, and production LLM-diff appliers (aider udiff, OpenAI apply_patch) all\ndiscard line numbers and locate by context, exactly as here. 12 specs cover\nhint disambiguation, ordered application over repeated sections, staleness,\nambiguity, whitespace drift, and header tolerance.\n"},{"type":4,"timestamp":1783005053,"nonce":"c/y+kkEOHZJ+KXavT4ySGT1H/NA=","title":"kref_patch — lenient unified diff, MCP-only (design spec)"},{"type":2,"timestamp":1783005053,"nonce":"9ovJvvvW4gvdYn+kx9eVPlR/QP8=","status":"accepted"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1783133417,"nonce":"2aMy4TvXuD6RTpVL0wdh3I1auLQ=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"retier"}]}